<HEADLINE>
<P>
VENTURA COUNTY NEWS ROUNDUP: MEINERS OAKS; 
</P>
<P>
CYCLIST, 8, HIT BY CAR IN STABLE CONDITION 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By CAROL WATSON 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
An 8-year-old boy who was hit by a car while riding his bicycle in Meiners Oaks 
was in stable condition Friday. 
</P>
<P>
Kristoffer Gonzales of Meiners Oaks broke his leg in the accident, which 
occurred at 5:20 p.m. Thursday while he was riding with friends, said Officer 
Jim Utter of the California Highway Patrol. 
</P>
<P>
Kristoffer was going south on Pueblo Avenue when he rode through a stop sign 
and in front of a car traveling west on Fernando Drive, Utter said. 
</P>
<P>
The boy was struck by the bumper of the car driven by Jeremy Ogletree, 16, of 
Oak View. 
</P>
<P>
Kristoffer was taken to Ojai Valley Community Hospital. 
</P>
<P>
He was later transferred to Ventura County Medical Center, where he was listed 
in stable condition Friday, a hospital spokeswoman said. 
</P>
<P>
No charges are expected to be brought against the driver, Utter said. CAROL 
WATSON 
</P>
</TEXT>
