187 words 
</P>
</LENGTH>
<HEADLINE>
<P>
VENTURA COUNTY NEWS ROUNDUP: THOUSAND OAKS; 
</P>
<P>
2 MEN CHARGED IN MOLESTATION CASES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By CAROL WATSON 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A 21-year-old man has pleaded guilty to child molestation charges, and a 
25-year-old man was arrested on suspicion of a similar crime in the Thousand 
Oaks area, authorities said Friday. 
</P>
<P>
Emilio De Jesus Herrera, 21, pleaded guilty to charges of sodomy and oral 
copulation and will be sentenced at a later date, said Ventura County Sheriff's 
Detective Bill Stovall. 
</P>
<P>
He was being held at the Ventura County Jail in lieu of $50,000 bail. 
</P>
<P>
Herrera befriended a 3-year-old boy on July 23 at an apartment complex at 1710 
W. Hillcrest Drive in Newbury Park, Stovall said. 
</P>
<P>
Herrera, who does landscape work in the area, gave the child a bike ride to the 
back of the complex, where he molested the boy, Stovall said. 
</P>
<P>
In a separate case, Martin Corona Reynosa, 25, was arrested on suspicion of 
lewd acts and penetration with a foreign object and was being held at the 
Ventura County Jail on $50,000 bail. 
</P>
<P>
Reynosa was a guest at a house on Calle Pensamiento in Thousand Oaks when he 
molested a 5-year-old girl, Stovall said. 
</P>
<P>
He was arrested after attempting to run from officers at his house, Stovall 
said. CAROL WATSON 
</P>
</TEXT>
