<HEADLINE>
<P>
SAVINGS AND LOAN CRISIS AND FREE MARKET FORCES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
So now our government technocrats are talking seriously about further 
deregulation of the banking system in this country. Just bear in mind that when 
the S&amp;Ls were deregulated under Jimmy Carter, our Congress lifted the FDIC 
insurance from $40,000 on deposits to $100,000. 
</P>
<P>
We didn't know they had decided to gamble with our money. 
</P>
<P>
They say we must deregulate the banks if they are to remain competitive on an 
international level. So, OK, but let the banks buy their own insurance and pass 
the cost on to their big depositors. The majority of people in this country 
have less than $1,000 on deposit or in savings. Why, then, should we agree to 
back the big boys plays. 
</P>
<P>
LAURELLA A. CROSS 
</P>
<P>
Irvine 
</P>
</TEXT>
