<P>
SAN DIEGO COUNTY DIGEST: EAST COUNTY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A Jeep hauling a rented trailer overturned on Interstate 8 early Friday, 
killing the driver and injuring his passenger. 
</P>
<P>
Matthew Kopchak, 20, was dead at the scene with massive head injuries from the 
1 a.m. accident, which occurred in the westbound lanes of I-8 where it crosses 
Crestwood Road in southeastern San Diego County. 
</P>
<P>
Ronald Nanne, 18, suffered minor injuries and was taken to Sharp Memorial 
Hospital. 
</P>
<P>
The two friends were from Plainfield, N.J., and had been driving cross-country, 
said Deputy Coroner Robert Engel. 
</P>
<P>
Kopchak "lost control of the Jeep, struck a guardrail, and the Jeep and a 
U-Haul trailer overturned," Engel said. 
</P>
<P>
Nanne is in good condition at the hospital with a broken finger, said 
spokeswoman Gwen Barnett. 
</P>
