METRO DIGEST / LOCAL NEWS IN BRIEF: SUSPECT ARRESTED AFTER OFFICER FIRES 2 
SHOTS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A narcotics suspect who allegedly attempted to run over an undercover police 
officer surrendered Friday after the Bell Gardens officer opened fire, 
authorities said. 
</P>
<P>
The suspect, Jesus Soto, 30, of Huntington Park, allegedly tried to run down 
the officer with his car on the Manchester Boulevard on-ramp to the southbound 
Harbor Freeway in Los Angeles about 4:30 p.m., Bell Gardens Police Sgt. Fred 
Freeman said. 
</P>
<P>
The unidentified officer fired two rounds, but both shots missed Soto and 
struck his car, Freeman said. 
</P>
<P>
Soto surrendered and was taken to Men's Central Jail, where he was booked on 
suspicion of assault with a deadly weapon against a peace officer, Freeman 
said. Narcotics-related charges against Soto were pending. 
</P>
<P>
The incident caused the closure of the southbound on-ramp for three hours. 
</P>
