<HEADLINE>
<P>
BRIEFLY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Service Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
FundAmerica Suspends Marketing: Irvine-based FundAmerica said it is suspending 
all membership sales until it revises its practices to the satisfaction of 
regulators in the eight states where it does business. The company is facing 
criminal charges of fraud and running an illegal lottery in Florida. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Column; Brief 
</P>
</TYPE>
<SUBJECT>
<P>
FUNDAMERICA; SECURITIES FRAUD; LOTTERIES 
</P>
</SUBJECT>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> LA081190-0114 </DOCNO>
<DOCID> 260442 </DOCID>
