Justice Department Reviews La Opinion Deal: The antitrust division has notified 
Times Mirror Co. that it has begun an investigation to determine the legality 
of the media company's proposed purchase of a 50% stake in La Opinion, a 
Spanish-language newspaper in Los Angeles. Justice officials asked the Los 
Angeles-based media company, which owns the Los Angeles Times and other 
publications, to delay completion of the transaction and to preserve all 
documents and records relating to the deal. 
