<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: SANTA ANA; 
</P>
<P>
ANTIQUE CAR PARADE FEATURES 200 AUTOS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Automobiles from decades gone by will weave their way through Santa Ana today 
during the 15th annual Antique Car Classic Parade. 
</P>
<P>
Sponsored by the city and South Coast Village, the event will feature about 200 
vintage cars from the 1920s to the 1970s. 
</P>
<P>
The cars will compete for best of show and for prizes in 20 other categories. 
</P>
<P>
The event begins at 10 a.m., with judging at Centennial Park at the corner of 
Edinger Avenue and Fairview Road. At noon, a parade of cars, along with a 
police escort, will proceed south on Fairview to Sunflower Avenue east, then to 
South Coast Village, at Sunflower and Plaza Drive. 
</P>
<P>
Jeff Ervine, disk jockey at KWIZ in Santa Ana, will be the grand marshal. 
Several members of the City Council are expected to make appearances. 
</P>
<P>
The cars will be on free public view in the parking lot of South Coast Village 
from 12:30 to 4 p.m. 
</P>
</TEXT>
