<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: SEAL BEACH; 
</P>
<P>
2 MEN SHOT DURING ON-RAMP ARGUMENT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Two men were shot and wounded early Friday morning as they argued with 
occupants of another car on an on-ramp to the San Diego Freeway. 
</P>
<P>
Leif Danielson, 22, of Greeley, Colo., was shot in the left foot, and Kenneth 
Miller, 22, of Costa Mesa was shot in the left thigh about 2:25 a.m., police 
said. 
</P>
<P>
Both were taken to Los Alamitos Medical Center, said Seal Beach police 
dispatcher Carl Liebold. 
</P>
<P>
Danielson remained in the hospital Friday after undergoing surgery, while 
Miller was treated and released, a hospital spokeswoman said. 
</P>
<P>
Danielson and Miller were heading onto the southbound lanes of the San Diego 
Freeway at the 7th Street on-ramp when they got into a confrontation with the 
occupants of a late-model, red Pontiac Trans-Am, Liebold said. 
</P>
<P>
One of the unidentified occupants in the Pontiac suddenly opened fire, striking 
Danielson and Miller, he said. 
</P>
<P>
Police found Danielson and Miller bleeding in their stopped car when they 
responded to calls from an unidentified witness. Liebold said police 
investigators did not know the nature of the dispute or whether the victims 
knew the assailants. 
</P>
</TEXT>
